#    season management framework. This ensures all systems transition together
#    and maintain consistent seasonal progression.
#
#    IMPORTANT - CONSOLIDATED SEASON ARCHITECTURE:
#    =============================================
#    The active season is controlled by a SINGLE source:
#      1. DarkChaos.ActiveSeasonID config setting (this file) - PREFERRED
#      2. dc_seasons table in CharacterDatabase (season_state = 1)
#    
#    Secondary tables exist for system-specific configuration:
#      - dc_mplus_seasons (WorldDB): M+ affix schedules, featured dungeons
#      - dc_hlbg_seasons (WorldDB): HLBG-specific seasonal settings
#    
#    These SECONDARY tables should NOT be queried for "which season is active"
#    All C++ code should use DarkChaos::GetActiveSeasonId() helper from:
#      #include "DC/CrossSystem/DCSeasonHelper.h"
#
#    Subsystems:
#    - Seasonal Rewards: Token/essence rewards from activities
#    - Mythic+: Seasonal affixes and dungeons
#    - Item Upgrades: Season-based upgrade paths
#    - Hinterland BG: Seasonal statistics and rankings
#
###########################################################################

#
#    DarkChaos.ActiveSeasonID
#        Description: Global active season ID for all seasonal systems
#                     When changed, ALL systems transition to the new season together.
#                     This is the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for season management.
#                     
#                     All systems use this value via DarkChaos::GetActiveSeasonId():
#                     - SeasonalRewards (token/essence rewards)
#                     - Mythic+ (seasonal affixes and dungeons)
#                     - Item Upgrades (season-based progression)
#                     - Hinterland BG (seasonal statistics)
#                     - Custom Login (starter token type)
#                     - DC-Welcome addon (season display)
#                     
#                     To change the active season:
#                     1. Update this config value and restart server, OR
#                     2. Use .dc season set <id> command (if implemented), OR
#                     3. Update dc_seasons table (season_state = 1 for active)
#                     
#        Default:     1 (Season 1)
#        Range:       1 - 99
#
DarkChaos.ActiveSeasonID = 1

